review_comments.body:
In my experience, using arbitrary short sleeps less than a few seconds is not sufficient and, increasing the sleep time, unnecessarily increases the build time, which can be frustrating. I prefer to use a "smart" sleep; most of the spring-integration-ip tests have something like this...

``` java
    private void waitListening(TcpInboundGateway gateway) throws Exception {
        int n = 0;
        while (!gateway.isListening()) {
            Thread.sleep(100);
            if (n++ > 100) {
                throw new Exception("Gateway failed to listen");
            }
        }

    }
```

which waits for up to 10 seconds buts exits as soon as we are ready.

